channel.title: Portforwarding Help Needed!
channel.description:
Hello All,
I've learned a lot lately on rs2 private servers all thanks to the people here, and myself for having a better understanding on what tutorials to google hahah..
But, I've came to another stop. . . Port fowarding! :eek:
SO I thought sence you all gave me such good advice before that you could give me good advice again! :)
So I have a Belkin F5D7234-4 (v1) router, and I was wondering if you all could tell me how to port forward it so i could distribute my rs2 private server.
What I'm asking is can you give me details on how to open up a port forward with all the details? And, where in the files I would go so they njust start the client, and start playing!
Thank you all very much for all, and any help!!
-TMC

item.title: Portforwarding Help Needed!
item.dc:creator: @TheMonkeyCreator TheMonkeyCreator
item.description:
@TheMonkeyCreator wrote:

Ok you need to download a client with an IP changer, or a client that has the IP option. So DL a client and run your source (LEAVE IT OPEN) minimize it, run your client, when it has the log in screen scroll down to IP Address or IP or something like that. It is below Password. Change that to your IP. Example:

Password: ****** (your password)
IP Address: example.no-ip.biz (or whatever your IP is)
[/quote]
So, your saying I’m going to have to find a client with a ip changer and that I cant just go into a fie or something.

And, i tried that with one that did have a ip changer and changed the ip to monkeyscape.no-ip.biz but it didn’t work…

Can anyone help with that too?

Do I need to set something up in it? Also I have downloaded the little program thing that came with the no-ip thing.

-TMC

item.title: Portforwarding Help Needed!
item.dc:creator: @staticfish1 staticfish1
item.description:
@staticfish1 wrote:

[quote=“TheMonkeyCreator, post:9, topic:313186”][quote author=staticfish1 link=topic=409690.msg3023310#msg3023310 date=1257718774]
If you want to change something that happens in game like a command you would go into client.java in your source folder. For example lets say you wanted to change the starter message of the server to Welcome to Monkeyscape! You would search for the current welcome message by hitting Ctrl+f in client.java and search for Welcome to. If you have a current welcome messgae it will be in here. So to find your current welcome message, go on your sever and log in. If it says in the chat box “Welcome to examplescape” that is what you would search in client.java. If it said “Potato” in the chat box when you logged in, that is what you would search for in client.java. Now save and compile. If you get compile errors try to change the text inside to your JDK version (jdk1.1.0_16) or whatever. You can find this out by going to C:\Program Files\Java\YOURVERSIONHERE. Input that number into your compile where it looks like it should go.

Omg lol. Sorry if that wasnt to easy to understand.
[/quote]
Well that helped with another problem I had lolz…

But, what I meant was I’ve got my port forward done, but where do I put the i.p. or what ever so other people can play?[/quote]
Ok you need to download a client with an IP changer, or a client that has the IP option. So DL a client and run your source (LEAVE IT OPEN) minimize it, run your client, when it has the log in screen scroll down to IP Address or IP or something like that. It is below Password. Change that to your IP. Example:
Username: TheMonkeyCreator (your Username)
Password: ****** (your password)
IP Address: example.no-ip.biz (or whatever your IP is)

item.title: Portforwarding Help Needed!
item.dc:creator: @Owner_Of_GdogScape Owner_Of_GdogScape
item.description:
@Owner_Of_GdogScape wrote:

First off if you have vista type in cmd in the start bar, right click on it and select run as administrator.
Then type in “ipconfig”
and look for somthing like this “IPv4…192.168.1.1**” (The “*” will be part of you’re ip adress)
you will need the last 3 numbers for later.

Go into your router, if its linksys you gotta type 192.168.1.1 in your web browser.
Then go into “Applications and gaming”
you’ll see somthing like
“Application-----Start----End-----Protocol----IP Adress----Enable”
And under application put “server” under Start put “43594” or you can have it as 5555. and under end put “43594”
Under protocol select “Both” but this should be set already. under IP Adress put the last three numbers (As I showed you above)
it should look like this “192.168.1.1**”
Then you should be done! just check the enable box, and save. Hope you have fun with you’re server!

item.dc:creator: @TheMonkeyCreator TheMonkeyCreator
item.description:
@TheMonkeyCreator wrote:

staticfish1:

You did it right and click the “Both” option. Go into your windows firewall and choose allow a program through. Add Port. Name it what ever you named it on your router. Make the port 43594. Click TCP. Accept. Click OK on all the windows.

Tyvm!

Si Force:

Follow the guide here, it should help you with the various steps, etc.

That link also sorta helped lolz.

Now to the last part of my question. . In the private servers what do I change and where do I change it?

Like do I change a file in the server files or the client files, and what files?

Again thank you very much!

-TMC
